(118, 1, '2014-10-13 11:10:57', '2014-10-13 09:10:57', '<!--:sk--><strong>Dvno</strong>\r\n\r\nPsal sa rok 1953, ke pri Slovenskej vysokej kole technickej v Bratislave vznikol amatrsky umeleck sbor. Zpvodne estrdneho sboru sa vyvinulo teleso so samostatnou folklrnou zlokou, spevckym zborom a komornm orchestrom. U vtedy bolo hlavnm poslanm telesa pestova, udriava a scnicky rozvja umeleck hodnoty slovenskho folklru. V praxi to znamenalo spracovvanie udovch tancov a zvykov, upravovanie udovch piesn i hudby z rznych reginov Slovenska pre umeleck scnu. Vprvch rokoch fungovania bol predmetom zujmu predovetkm tradin folklr. Neskr - v sedemdesiatych rokoch vzniklo niekoko programovch blokov, ako naprklad Ze Zhora - o mladosti, krse alske (ch. Cyril Zlek, h.Vteslav Volav), i blok zo severnho aria, ktorho svin tanen krecie m sbor v repertori dodnes.\r\n\r\nSvoj rukopis zanechalo na folklrnom sbore TECHNIK mnoho vznamnch choreografov a pedaggov. Popri dlhoronom choreografovi Cyrilovi Zlekovi s dleitmi menami umeleck vedci Ing. Pavol Olekk, RNDr. Miroslav Kapasn i pedaggovia Milan evk, Nataa Hesekov, Janka Grskov, Zorka Martincov. Vtomto obdob reprezentoval sbor nau kultru naprklad vPortugalsku (1969), vo Vekej Britnii (1983), v Andorre(1987), na Sardnii (1989), na Korzike(1991), vKanade (1994), vGrcku (1995) vo Franczku (1996), vechch (1997), vBelgicku (1998), vHolandsku (1999) i vTaliansku (1999).\r\n\r\n<strong>Ne/dvno</strong>\r\n\r\nFolklrny sbor Technik jei dnes aktvnou asou umeleckho telesa psobiaceho pri Slovenskej technickej univerzite vBratislave. Tvor ho udov hudba, spevcka a tanen zloka. Ciele sa nezmenili  vytrvalo sa venuje udriavaniu, pestovaniu ascnickmu podaniu slovenskch folklrnych tradci. Draz kladie naloklne a regionlne pecifik tradinch prejavov vjednotlivch reginoch\r\n\r\nV roku 1998 sa umeleckho vedenia ujalaubica Mekov. V rmci tanenej zloky ho aktvne v septembri 2009 prevzal viacron pedagg a choreograf sboru Frantiek Morong, kedy sa . Mekov ujala postu riaditeky sboru.Psobenie F. Moronga trvalo do augusta 2012, kedy sa umeleck vedenie znova vrtilo do rk . Mekovej. udov hudba pracovala pod vedenm viacerch talentovanch muzikantov, akmi s Peter Obuch, i Juraj Murn avnedvnej minulosti prela pod umeleck vedenie tefana Molotu a.h. Spevcku zloku vedie Lucia Turiniov. Krojov dielu spravuje Denisa Cickov.\r\n\r\nZkladn repertor sboru tvoria hudobno - tanen sla z ierneho Balogu, Oovej, Zmutova, Vynch Raslavc, Krivian, Vajnor, Trenna, Kubrej, Hornch Prian, uavy, Rejdovej, Kalotaszgu at.\r\n\r\nspechy zoalo teleso predovetkm s hudobno-tanenm blokom z Vajnor De sa dobr vno rodz (ch.: . Mekov a F. Morong, h..: P.Obuch) a tancami z Prian Vtka po per, tanec po muzike (ch.: manelia Morongovci, h..: P. Obuch), sa stal Technik Lauretom Akademickho Zvolena (2005, 2007) a Akademickej Nitry (2008). V roku 2010 sa Technik z choreografiou B. Morongovej "Ktoe by vs nemiloval Rejdovianky" stal optovne Lauretom Akademickej Nitry.\r\n\r\n<strong>Dnes</strong>\r\n\r\nMinul rok sbor oslvil u 60. vroie zaloenia aoslvil to celkom novm programom Technikarska kopa, ktor bol uveden vo vekej sle v Istropolise.\r\n\r\nRok 2014 priniesol viacer zmeny vzostavch iveden telesa. Umeleckho patrontu sa ujal mlad ikovn tanen pedagg achoreograf sboru Igor Hajduk. Vsasnosti obohacuje profesionlny autorsk kolektv FS Technik repertor sboru ozaujmav nov sla, ktormi vs radi pote pri najbliej prleitosti.<!--:--><!--:en--><b>A long time ago</b>\r\n\r\nIt was in 1953, when an amateurish artistic ensemble was formed near the Slovak Technical University in Bratislava. Having been avariety ensemble, it developed into abody with its own folklore section, choir and achamber orchestra. Even then, the main role of the ensemble was to cherish, maintain and scenically develop artistic values of Slovak folklore. In practice, it meant processing of folk dances and customs, editing of folk songs and music from different regions of Slovakia, for the art scene. In the first years of functioning the subject of interest was primarily traditional folklore. Later  in seventies anumber of slots were formed such as From Zhorie  about youth, beauty and love (Choreography- Cyril Zlek, music  Vteslav Volav), or aslot from northern ari, whose agile dance creations are hitherto in the repertory of ensemble.\r\n\r\nMany eminent choreographers and pedagogues have left their hand-writing on the folklore ensemble TECHNIK. Along alongstanding choreographer Cyril Zlek, the important names worth mentioning are art director Ing. Pavol Olekk, RNDr. Miroslav Kapasn or pedagogues Milan evk, Nataa Hesekov, Janka Grskov and Zorka Martincov. During this period the ensemble represented our culture for instance in Portugal (1969), in Great Britain (1983), in Andorra (1987), in Sardinia (1989), in Corsica (1991), in Canada (1994), in Greece (1995), in France (1996), in the Czech republic (1997), in Belgium (1998), in the Netherlands (1999) or in Italy (1999).\r\n\r\n<b>Recently</b>\r\n\r\nFolklore ensemble Technik is nowadays an active part of an artistic body operating near the Slovak Technical University in Bratislava. It is formed by aFolk band together with a singing and a dance section. The aims have not changed  persistently, the ensemble is dedicated to maintaining, cherishing and scenic presentation of Slovak folklore traditions. The emphasis is put on local and regional specifications of traditional expressions in separate regions.\r\n\r\nIn 1998, ubica Mekov became art director and in September 2009 she undertook the post of director of the whole ensemble. Within the dance section, Frantiek Morong, amultiannual pedagogue and choreographer of the ensemble became its art director the same year. His function lasted until August 2012, when the art direction was returned into hands of . Mekov. The Folk band worked under leadership of several talented musicians such asPeter Obuch or Juraj Murn, though, for many years under supervision of tefan Molota (as a guest). The singing section is led by Lucia Turiniov. The costume workshop is administered by Denisa Cickov.\r\n\r\nEssential repertory of the ensemble consists of music-dance numbers from ierny Balog, Oov, Zmutov, Vyn Raslavice, Krivany, Vajnory, Trenn, Kubra, Horn Prany, uava, Rejdov Kalotaszg etc.\r\n\r\nThe biggest success of the body was principally amusic-dance slot from Vajnory with name Where the good wine is yielded (ch.: . Mekov and F. Morong, m.: P.Obuch) and dances from Prany A bird according to feathers, dance according to music  (ch.: spouses Morongs, m.: P.Opuch). Moreover, Technik became aLaureate of Academic Zvolen (2005, 2007) and Academic Nitra (2008). In 2010, Technik repeatedly became the Laureate of Academic Nitra with achoreography of B. Morongov: Who wouldnt love you, girls from Rejdov.\r\n\r\n<b>Today</b>\r\n\r\nPrevious year, the ensemble celebrated the 60th anniversary since its formation with acompletely new programme Technik heap, which was introduced in great hall in Istropolis.\r\n\r\nYear 2014 brought many changes both in lineup and leadership of the body. The art patronage was undertaken by ayoung, talented dance pedagogue and choreograph of the ensemble, Igor Hajdik. In the present, the professional composite author FS Technik enriches repertory of the ensemble with new interesting numbers, with which it will be delighted to please you at the earliest opportunity.<!--:--><!--:de--><p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Dvno</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Psal sa rok 1953, ke pri Slovenskej vysokej kole technickej v Bratislave vznikol amatrsky umeleck sbor. Zpvodne estrdneho sboru sa vyvinulo teleso so samostatnou folklrnou zlokou, spevckym zborom a komornm orchestrom. U vtedy bolo hlavnm poslanm telesa pestova, udriava a scnicky rozvja umeleck hodnoty slovenskho folklru. V praxi to znamenalo spracovvanie udovch tancov a zvykov, upravovanie udovch piesn i hudby z rznych reginov Slovenska pre umeleck scnu. Vprvch rokoc